3.-Database-Read-Replica.content:
A deep-dive map of database horizontal scaling. Covers how read replicas are provisioned as synchronized, read-only mirrors of a primary database instance, the uptime and performance benefits of offloading read-heavy query traffic away from the primary write node, and the foundational mental model required before configuring HAProxy to route traffic across replica nodes.
Target Audience: Software Engineer 2 | Mid-Level Backend Mastery
Core Domain: Distributed Systems, Advanced Spring Framework Architecture, and Infrastructure Scaling

🍃 Core Architectural Concepts &amp; Study Guide
